info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued February 21 at 3:30AM PST until February 21 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING... ...HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...For the Coastal Flood Advisory, minor coastal flooding expected. For the High Surf Advisory, large breaking waves of 19 to 23 feet expected in the surf zone today with waves 19 or 20 feet tonight. * WHERE...North Coast and Central Coast zones. * WHEN...For the Coastal Flood Advisory, from 4 AM to 10 AM PST Tuesday. For the High Surf Advisory, from 4 AM Tuesday to 4 AM PST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Minor coastal flooding due to tidal overflow is expected around high tide. This may lead to flooding of parking lots, parks, and roads, with only isolated road closures expected. Dangerous swimming and surfing conditions and localized beach erosion. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Inundation of up to 0.5 feet above ground level is possible along shorelines and low-lying coastal areas.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property. Inundation above ground level refers to the height above the Mean Higher High Water (MHHW) level. Inexperienced swimmers should remain out of the water due to dangerous surf conditions.
